503
00:39:00,237 --> 00:39:02,655
And a total fucking mystery.

504
00:39:02,656 --> 00:39:03,948
I hate it.

505
00:39:03,949 --> 00:39:05,950
Maybe you'll let me teach you someday.

506
00:39:05,951 --> 00:39:07,611
yeah. sure.

507
00:39:08,496 --> 00:39:10,705
I thought of getting a board together.

508
00:39:10,706 --> 00:39:13,583
Well, I'm the right man. I'm the guy that can get things.

509
00:39:13,584 --> 00:39:15,168
We might do business on a board.

510
00:39:15,169 --> 00:39:18,449
But I want to carve the pieces myself.

511
00:39:38,429 --> 00:39:40,693
- Rita Hayworth. - What? One side in alabaster, the opposing side in soapstone. What do you think? I think it'll take years. Well, years I got. What I don't have are the rocks. Pickings are pretty slim in the yard. Pebbles, mostly. Andy, we're getting to be kinda friends, aren't we? Yeah, I guess.

512
00:39:40,694 --> 00:39:43,134
Can I ask you something?

513
00:39:43,197 --> 00:39:45,277
Why did you do it?

514
00:39:46,408 --> 00:39:50,348
I'm innocent, Red. Just like everybody else here.

515
00:39:54,583 --> 00:39:56,783
What are you in for?

516
00:39:58,671 --> 00:39:59,754
Murder.

517
00:39:59,755 --> 00:40:01,256
Same as you.

518
00:40:01,257 --> 00:40:02,797
Innocent?

519
00:40:05,094 --> 00:40:07,834
Only guilty man in Shawshank.

520
00:41:06,655 --> 00:41:08,323
Where's the canary?

521
00:41:08,324 --> 00:41:09,657
How did you know?

522
00:41:09,658 --> 00:41:10,908
How did I know what?

523
00:41:10,909 --> 00:41:13,409
So, you don't know? Come.

524
00:41:16,081 --> 00:41:19,241
This is where the canary is, Johnny.

525
00:41:20,586 --> 00:41:25,486
Quite a surprise to hear a woman singing in my house, eh, Johnny?

526
00:41:27,509 --> 00:41:29,529
That's quite a...

527
00:41:29,970 --> 00:41:31,510
surprise.

528
00:41:34,141 --> 00:41:35,501
Red...

529
00:41:35,934 --> 00:41:37,810
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

530
00:41:37,811 --> 00:41:39,711
Here she comes.

531
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:42,690
This is the part I like - when she does that shit with her hair.

532
00:41:42,691 --> 00:41:45,693
Yeah, I know. I've seen it three times this month.

533
00:41:45,694 --> 00:41:47,779
Gilda, are you decent?

534
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:48,960
Me?

535
00:41:51,533 --> 00:41:53,733
Hah! God, I love it!

536
00:41:59,458 --> 00:42:03,336
I understand you're a man that knows how to get things.

537
00:42:03,337 --> 00:42:07,298
Yeah, I'm known to locate certain things from time to time. What do you want?

538
00:42:07,299 --> 00:42:09,739
- Rita Hayworth. - What?

539
00:42:09,885 --> 00:42:11,845
Can you get her?

540
00:42:12,805 --> 00:42:16,349
So, this is Johnny Farrell. I've heard a lot about you, Johnny.

