00:44:50,587 --> 00:44:53,627
All prisoners report for lockdown.

579
00:45:08,313 --> 00:45:09,613
What?

580
00:45:11,444 --> 00:45:12,864
(Gasps) [GASPING] 

581
00:45:16,238 --> 00:45:18,318
(Bogs cries in pain) 

582
00:45:22,077 --> 00:45:25,597
where's he going? hadley: grab his ankles.

583
00:45:26,373 --> 00:45:27,793
No! No!

584
00:45:28,959 --> 00:45:30,139
No!

585
00:45:30,419 --> 00:45:31,836
[BOGS GROANING] Help me...

586
00:45:31,837 --> 00:45:33,317
(Punching and screaming) Aaarghh!

587
00:45:35,424 --> 00:45:38,175
two things never happened again after that.

588
00:45:38,176 --> 00:45:42,056
The Sisters never laid a finger on Andy again...

589
00:45:42,222 --> 00:45:45,022
..and Bogs never walked again.

590
00:45:46,059 --> 00:45:49,562
They transferred him to a minimum-security hospital upstate.

591
00:45:49,563 --> 00:45:55,359
To my knowledge, he lived out the rest of his days drinking his food through a straw.

592
00:45:55,360 --> 00:46:01,157
I'm thinking Andy could use a nice welcome back when he gets out of the infirmary.

593
00:46:01,158 --> 00:46:05,878
Sounds good to us. I figure we owe him that much for the beer.

594
00:46:06,330 --> 00:46:09,010
The man likes to play chess.

595
00:46:09,082 --> 00:46:11,582
Let's get him some rocks.

596
00:46:43,575 --> 00:46:44,995
Guys...

597
00:46:45,535 --> 00:46:48,155
I got one. I got one. Look.

598
00:46:50,332 --> 00:46:52,500
Heywood, that isn't soapstone.

599
00:46:52,501 --> 00:46:54,794
And it ain't alabaster, either.

600
00:46:54,795 --> 00:46:56,504
What are you, a fucking geologist?

601
00:46:56,505 --> 00:46:58,631
He's right. It ain't.

602
00:46:58,632 --> 00:46:59,966
Well, what the hell is it?

603
00:46:59,967 --> 00:47:01,807
a horse apple.

604
00:47:02,594 --> 00:47:05,994
- Bullshit. - No, horse shit. Petrified.

605
00:47:05,806 --> 00:47:07,646
(Horse whinnies) 

606
00:47:12,104 --> 00:47:14,124
(Men laugh) oh, jesus christ!

607
00:47:15,065 --> 00:47:16,605
Oh, damn!

608
00:47:17,109 --> 00:47:21,649
despite a few hitches, the boys came through in fine style.

609
00:47:22,280 --> 00:47:24,991
And by the weekend he was due back, we had enough rocks

610
00:47:24,992 --> 00:47:27,792
to keep him busy till rapture.

611
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:30,913
I also got a big shipment in that week.

612
00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:33,354
Cigarettes. Chewing gum.

613
00:47:33,542 --> 00:47:35,126
Sipping whisky.

614
00:47:35,127 --> 00:47:38,754
Playing cards with naked ladies on them. You name it.

615
00:47:38,755 --> 00:47:42,095
And of course, the most important item.

616
00:47:43,468 --> 00:47:45,788
Rita Hayworth herself.

617
00:48:19,713 --> 00:48:22,573
ok, look alive! open all tiers.

618
00:48:22,632 --> 00:48:25,051
(Furtively) heads up. they're tossing the cells.

619
00:48:25,052 --> 00:48:28,212
Heads up. They're tossing the cells.

620
00:48:29,431 --> 00:48:30,671
119.

621
00:48:32,809 --> 00:48:34,049
123.

622
00:48:35,562 --> 00:48:37,642
(Guards calling out) 

623
00:48:43,945 --> 00:48:45,725
On your feet.

624
00:48:47,532 --> 00:48:49,372
Face the wall.

625
00:49:23,902 --> 00:49:26,822
turn around and face the warden.

626
00:49:31,701 --> 00:49:34,621
Pleased to see you reading this.

627
00:49:35,163 --> 00:49:37,483
Any favorite passages?

628
00:49:38,500 --> 00:49:43,880
Watch ye, therefore, for ye know not when the master of the house cometh.

629
00:49:44,673 --> 00:49:46,333
Mark 13:35.

630
00:49:47,634 --> 00:49:50,074
I always liked that one.

631
00:49:50,387 --> 00:49:51,971
But I prefer...

632
00:49:51,972 --> 00:49:54,592
I'm the light of the world.

633
00:49:54,808 --> 00:49:58,435
He that followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life.

634
00:49:58,436 --> 00:50:00,996
John, Chapter 8, Verse 12.

635
00:50:01,106 --> 00:50:04,626
I hear you're good with numbers. How nice.

636
00:50:05,694 --> 00:50:08,254
A man should have a skill.

637
00:50:09,865 --> 00:50:12,005
Wanna explain this?

638
00:50:12,409 --> 00:50:16,912
It's called a rock blanket. It's for shaping and polishing rocks.

639
00:50:16,913 --> 00:50:19,293
A little hobby of mine.

640
00:50:27,299 --> 00:50:28,719
(Inhales) 

641
00:50:29,718 --> 00:50:32,803
It's pretty clean. Some contraband here,

642
00:50:32,804 --> 00:50:35,904
but nothing to get in a twist over.

643
00:50:38,727 --> 00:50:41,527
I can't say I approve of this.

644
00:50:42,314 --> 00:50:44,274
But I suppose...

645
00:50:45,984 --> 00:50:48,484
..exceptions can be made.

646
00:50:58,246 --> 00:50:59,966
lock 'em up!

647
00:51:02,542 --> 00:51:04,502
I almost forgot.

648
00:51:04,586 --> 00:51:06,921
I'd hate to deprive you of this.

649
00:51:06,922 --> 00:51:09,242
Salvation lies within.

650
00:51:48,115 --> 00:51:50,923
But it'd be nice to have some company down here. Yes, sir. tossing cells was just an excuse. The truth is, Norton wanted to size Andy up. My wife made that in church group. Very nice, sir. Do you enjoy working in the laundry?

651
00:51:50,924 --> 00:51:52,716
No, sir, not especially.

652
00:51:52,717 --> 00:51:55,594
Perhaps we can find something more...

653
00:51:55,595 --> 00:51:58,635
befitting a man of your education.

654
00:52:02,020 --> 00:52:03,440
(Bird screeches) [CROWING] 

655
00:52:06,022 --> 00:52:07,773
Hey, Jake. Where's Brooks?

656
00:52:07,774 --> 00:52:09,074
Andy.

657
00:52:09,150 --> 00:52:12,010
I thought I heard you out here!

658
00:52:12,946 --> 00:52:14,613
(Chuckles) I've been reassigned to you.

659
00:52:14,614 --> 00:52:16,874
i know. they told me.

660
00:52:17,867 --> 00:52:20,035
Ain't that a kick in the head?

661
00:52:20,036 --> 00:52:22,621
Well, I'll give you the dime tour.

662
00:52:22,622 --> 00:52:24,102
Come on.

663
00:52:24,791 --> 00:52:26,871
Well, here she is.

664
00:52:27,043 --> 00:52:29,543
Shawshank Prison library.

665
00:52:29,671 --> 00:52:31,931
National Geographics.

666
00:52:32,632 --> 00:52:35,551
Reader's Digest condensed books.

667
00:52:35,552 --> 00:52:37,392
Louis L'Amour.

668
00:52:37,846 --> 00:52:39,686
Look Magazine.

669
00:52:40,056 --> 00:52:42,376
Erle Stanley Gardners.

670
00:52:42,642 --> 00:52:46,186
Every evening, I load up the cart and make my round.

671
00:52:46,187 --> 00:52:49,440
I enter the names on this clipboard here.

672
00:52:49,441 --> 00:52:52,661
Easy-peasy, Japanesey. Any questions?

673
00:52:52,986 --> 00:52:56,030
Brooks, how long have you been librarian?

674
00:52:56,031 --> 00:53:00,631
Oh...I come here in '05, and they made me librarian in 1912.

675
00:53:01,286 --> 00:53:04,747
And in all that time, have you ever had an assistant?

676
00:53:04,748 --> 00:53:07,416
No. No, not much to it, really.

677
00:53:07,417 --> 00:53:09,418
Well, why me? Why now?

678
00:53:09,419 --> 00:53:11,003
I don't know,

679
00:53:11,004 --> 00:53:14,340
but it'll be nice to have some company down here for a change.

680
00:53:14,341 --> 00:53:15,881
dufresne!

681
00:53:25,727 --> 00:53:28,347
That's him. That's the one.

682
00:53:35,362 --> 00:53:36,737
(Nervously) I'm Dekins.

683
00:53:36,738 --> 00:53:38,398
i was er...

684
00:53:39,282 --> 00:53:45,082
thinking about maybe setting up some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.

685
00:53:45,622 --> 00:53:46,922
Oh...

686
00:53:47,165 --> 00:53:48,525
I see.

687
00:53:50,293 --> 00:53:52,013
Well, erm...

688
00:53:53,546 --> 00:53:55,172
..why don't we have a seat,

689
00:53:55,173 --> 00:53:57,193
and talk it over?

690
00:53:59,803 --> 00:54:03,803
Brooks, do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?

691
00:54:14,192 --> 00:54:15,612
Thanks.

692
00:54:15,985 --> 00:54:17,285
So...

693
00:54:18,905 --> 00:54:20,685
Mr. Dekins...

694
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:26,036
And then Andy says to Mr. Dekins, Do you want your sons to go to Harvard,

695
00:54:26,037 --> 00:54:28,247
- or Yale? - He didn't say that?

696
00:54:28,248 --> 00:54:30,988
As God is my witness, he did!

697
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:34,461
Dekins just blinked for a second. Then he laughed himself silly.

698
00:54:34,462 --> 00:54:36,422
And afterwards he shook Andy's hand.

699
00:54:36,423 --> 00:54:37,843
My ass!

700
00:54:37,882 --> 00:54:39,174
(Laughs) Shook his hand.

701
00:54:39,175 --> 00:54:42,035
hell, i...i near soiled myself!

702
00:54:42,220 --> 00:54:47,933
All Andy needed was a suit and a tie and a little jiggly hula girl on his desk,

703
00:54:47,934 --> 00:54:49,560
Mr. Dufresne, if you please!

704
00:54:49,561 --> 00:54:52,181
Making a few friends, Andy?

705
00:54:52,355 --> 00:54:54,398
I wouldn't say friends.

706
00:54:54,399 --> 00:54:58,485
I'm a convicted murderer who provides sound financial planning.

707
00:54:58,486 --> 00:55:00,904
It's a wonderful pet to have.

708
00:55:00,905 --> 00:55:02,906
Got you out of the laundry, though.

709
00:55:02,907 --> 00:55:05,200
Well, it might do more than that.

710
00:55:05,201 --> 00:55:08,287
How about expanding the library? Get some new books in there.

711
00:55:08,288 --> 00:55:11,081
If you're gonna ask for something, ask for a pool table.

712
00:55:11,082 --> 00:55:13,625
- Right. - How do you expect to do that?

713
00:55:13,626 --> 00:55:18,166
I mean, get new books in here, Mr. Dufresne, if you please?

714
00:55:18,965 --> 00:55:21,465
(Laughter) [MEN CHUCKLING] Ask the Warden for funds.

715
00:55:22,135 --> 00:55:25,512
Son, son. Six wardens have been through here in my tenure,

716
00:55:25,513 --> 00:55:29,224
and I've learned one immutable, universal truth.

717
00:55:29,225 --> 00:55:30,934
Not one of them born...

718
00:55:30,935 --> 00:55:35,981
whose asshole wouldn't pucker up tighter than a snare drum when you asked them for funds.

719
00:55:35,982 --> 00:55:38,358
The budget's stretched thin, as it is.

720
00:55:38,359 --> 00:55:39,693
I see.

721
00:55:39,694 --> 00:55:43,322
Perhaps I could write to the State Senate and request funds from them.

722
00:55:43,323 --> 00:55:47,784
As far as they're concerned, there's only three ways to spend money when it comes to prisons:

723
00:55:47,785 --> 00:55:49,953
more walls, more bars and more guards.

724
00:55:49,954 --> 00:55:54,458
